OL,3,CGrandparents sentenced to life
OL,4,Cimprisonment for murder of Ethan Ives-
OL,5,CGriffiths
OL,7,F"What happened to Ethan has changed
OL,8,Feverything in my life. At times I
OL,9,Fdon't feel like that it's real that
OL,10,FEthan is no longer with us and I often
OL,11,Ffind myself thinking I can hear his
OL,12,Faffectionate laugh, and it reminds me
OL,13,Fwhat a beautiful son he was and how
OL,14,Flucky I was to be his dad."
OL,16,FHe continued: "Ethan will never be
OL,17,Fforgotten and will always live on in
OL,18,Four hearts and I have come to accept
OL,19,Fthat the cherished memories that I do
OL,20,Fhave, now give me comfort rather than
OL,21,Fpain and grief."
